<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="F" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Forego" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Forego,</orth> 1) to give up, renounce: <bibl n="shak. son 125.7" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 125, 7</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 3.3.12" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. III, 3, 12</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 3.1.207" default="NO" valid="yes">John III, 1, 207</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 1.3.160" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 I, 3, 160</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 4.212.160" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 212</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 3.2.423" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 III, 2, 423</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 5.8.9" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. V, 8, 9</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 2.2.308" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. II, 2, 308</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 3.7.46" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. III, 7, 46</bibl>.<lb />2) to forfeit: <cit><quote>mine eyes f. their light,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 228" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 228</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>let us not f. that for a trifle that was bought with blood,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 4.1.149" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A IV, 1, 149</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>